{
  "stem": "151.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "How do you know?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SOB My father said that he marked the date for himself because that night-- [CRYING] --he dreamt that he was in the woods and this black horse was running.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My brother's hair was very dark and beautiful black eyes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he says I grabbed this horse and the horse wiggled himself out of my way and ran.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when I woke up next morning, he said, I knew that my son escaped.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[CRYING]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After my father passed away, we both decided that we don't want to stay in Europe.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And in the meantime, Bernard, my husband, kept coming, visiting after that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when my father died, he told me that he promised my father that he's going to take care of me so he has to marry me.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And so we got married.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And a year later my sister-in-law had her first child and then the following year I had a child.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then we decided that we're going to leave Prague.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Bernard, my husband, had papers to come to the United States because he lived in Prague in 1939 as a student and he had a student visa to come to the United States to a sister.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he was caught in Holland by the Nazis by the Gestapo and was brought back and went through the whole concentration camp experience.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so the American government acknowledged his papers and so we were put on the quota.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But my brother couldn't so my brother went to France.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And in France the Haganah got a hold of him and they went to Palestine, which is now the state of Israel.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And even though we were lucky to find each other, we were again separated for 15 years.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
